This paper deals with Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) and their application in unsupervised image-to-image translation. The paper focuses on the role of the discriminator's receptive field in GANs, which is a key aspect of computer vision and image processing, making cs.CV the most likely category. The paper also discusses the effect of the discriminator architecture on semantic content retention, which is related to machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.LG and cs.AI likely categories as well. The paper also deals with diverse datasets, which could be related to graphics and multimedia (cs.MM) and computer graphics (cs.GR).
